/2023/08/bobbi-althoff-drake-interview-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/bobbi-althoff-drake-interview-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/bobbi-althoff-drake-interview-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p>一名 TikTok 用户因在床上对<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/drake">德雷克</a>进行的采访而走红。</p><p>社交媒体内容创作者兼播客 Bobbi Althoff 还采访过<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/tyga">Tyga</a> 、 <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/offset">Offset</a>和<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/lil-yachty">Lil Yachty</a>等明星。</p><p>早在七月，她就发布了与德雷克谈话的预告片段，其中显示两人在羽绒被下面聊天，并配文：“我与德雷克的采访的其余部分很快就会结束……”</p><p>完整视频在网上疯传，但后来被删除，引发了关于两人闹翻的谣言。</p><p>以下是有关 Bobbi Althoff 以及她对 Drake 的病毒式采访的所有信息。</p><h2>博比·阿尔索夫是谁？</h2><p> Bobbi Althoff 是一位 26 岁的 TikTok 用户，同时也是<em>《Really Good Podcast》的</em>主持人，她在该播客中采访说唱歌手和音乐明星。</p><p>她的个人资料之前充满了怀孕和新生儿的最新动态，但此后她改变了内容，并欢迎众多音乐明星加入播客麦克风。</p><p>她目前在 TikTok 上拥有 600 万粉丝、1.9 亿个赞和超过 1 亿次观看。 </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="我对德雷克的其余采访将于周一在我的频道上直播，所以请确保您已订阅" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/Fv8LZ_fUo64?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p>人们将她面无表情的采访风格和冷幽默与英国 YouTube 明星阿米莉亚·迪莫尔德伯格 (Amelia Dimoldenberg) 和她的系列<em>《鸡肉店约会》</em>进行比较，在该系列中，她采访了来自英国鸡肉店的音乐家、演员和流行文化明星。</p><p>阿尔托夫与客人的融洽关系在语气和风格上都很相似，期间她故意提出一些尴尬或干巴巴的问题。</p><h2>德雷克采访发生了什么？</h2><p> In Althoff&#39;s interview with Drake, the pair chatted to each other from a bed underneath a blanket, during which she asked questions like “Why do you follow so many people on Instagram?” and “Are you gonna buy me a flight home?” (per <em><a href="https://www.insider.com/drake-bobbi-althoff-podcast-friendship-explanation-what-happened-2023-8" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Cosmopolitan</a></em> ).</p><p> Speaking to the publication, Althoff&#39;s said: “I decided to just go for it and shoot my shot. I DMed Drake and asked if he wanted to be on my podcast, and he said yes. </p><blockquote class="tiktok-embed" cite="https://www.tiktok.com/@bobbialthoff/video/7266676297261223210" data-video-id="7266676297261223210" data-embed-from="oembed" style="max-width: 605px;min-width: 325px;" ><section> <a target="_blank" title="@bobbialthoff" href="https://www.tiktok.com/@bobbialthoff?refer=embed">@bobbialthoff</a></p><p> Really in my element here @ this guys concert</p><p> <a target="_blank" title="♬ original sound - Bobbi" href="https://www.tiktok.com/music/original-sound-7266714169683053355?refer=embed">♬ original sound – Bobbi</a></section></blockquote><p><script async src="https://www.tiktok.com/embed.js"></script></p><p> “He sent me his touring schedule, and I knew that I needed to make it happen fast, so my friend and I flew to Memphis two days after the original DM was sent to record the episode.”</p><p> The full interview has now been removed, but the shorter teasers are still on her <a href="https://www.youtube.com/@Thebobbialthoff" target="_blank" rel="noopener">YouTube channel</a> .</p><p> Another recent TikTok showed her looking bored and unimpressed at Drake&#39;s concert, which she captioned: “Really in my element here @ this guys concert.”</p><p> The removal of the videos has led to speculation about an apparent feud, with some wondering if Drake or his label were upset by her reaction to the show. Others, however, have wondered if it&#39;s just a publicity stunt. Neither Drake nor Althoff has commented on this.</p><p> Elaborating on her interview approach with <em>Cosmopolitan</em> , Althoff said: “There&#39;s no prep, and that&#39;s the fun of it.</p><p> “They know it&#39;s a character, and we just wing it. It&#39;s not a real interview. I&#39;m not trying to get hard-hitting information about you — I&#39;m not trying to uncover anything. It&#39;s just a conversation. It&#39;s really a parody of a good interview.”</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/tv/who-is-bobbi-althoff-the-tiktoker-who-interviewed-drake-in-bed-3483892">Who is Bobbi Althoff, the TikToker who interviewed Drake in bed?</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
